body:
@markusweimer I pushed the updates
- We now use a wake stage in place of an executorService in running the SchedulerDriver
- Migrated to Avro

@jwang98052 
How do we build the .NET code? How do we integrate with CI for building and testing this code?

There's a binary file in the pull request. We should avoid putting any binary file.

Agreed, the `NuGet.exe` needs to go. I believe Visual Studio will be able to download our dependencies even if it is missing.

@bgchun The code is built using `msbuild` or Visual Studio. @beysims has an integration between that and Maven such that a `mvn -PDotNet clean install` builds the Java and .NET code bases in one go. I suggest to do another PR for that integration.

Theoretically, that integration means that we can build this code on the Windows build servers. But given that even the Java builds fail reliably on that, I suggest we should move the CI setup for the .NET code to another Jira.
